    <text>
        <body>       

                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>W. De Wolf&#44;<lb/>
                MANUFACTURER OF<lb/>
                Furs&#44; Umbrellas and Parasols&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>6 South Eighth Street&#44;<lb/>								
                BELOW MARKET.<lb/></p>								
            <p>39 South Eighth Street&#44;<lb/>
                ABOVE CHESTNUT.<lb/>
                Philadelphia&#44; Sep 23 1889<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev&#58; Dr S&#58; Morais	Present<lb/>
                Rev Sir&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>In the name of my brothers &#38; sisters I<lb/> would politely request you to kindly write the inscription<lb/> for the Gravestone of my deceased mother &#38; at foot I beg leave<lb/> to give you the necessary Data in English&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>We take the liberty to trouble you for the reason of the Keen interest<lb/> you have always evinced to our family&#44; and that our late<lb/> lamented mother having during her life been a very religious<lb/> woman&#44; we are sure that had she had the option of electing<lb/> who should write the inscription for her tomb&#44; she would have<lb/> named you&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>Finally I would beg to request you most politely &#38; urgently to<lb/> send me the manuscript at your <hi rend="underline">very earliest</hi> convenience<lb/> as one of my brothers must of necessity leave the City on an<lb/> eight months business trip&#44; on the day after Kippur &#38; since<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>he naturally desires to assist at the ceremony of &#34;setting the<lb/> stone&#34; we have to have it done a day or two before Kippur<lb/> thus giving the stone cutter but a f&#91;&#63;&#93; to finish the<lb/> words&#45;&#45;<lb/></p>
            <p>We would like to have this inscription to correspond<lb/> as nearly as possible with that of on the tomb of our<lb/> late lamented father &#38; beg to enclose copy of the<lb/> inscription on that tomb.<lb/></p>
            <p>I remain Rev&#58; Sir<lb/> Your most obedient Servant<lb/> W. De. Wolf<lb/></p>
                
            <p>In Memory of<lb/>
                Rachel<lb/>
                Wife of Hyman S De Wolf.<lb/>
                Born in Amsterdam&#44; Holland&#44;<lb/>
                April 14<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1812.<lb/>
                F Died . . . . . . . . . . . . .<lb/>
                corresponding with<lb/>
                March 12<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1889<lb/>
                &#40;F Mother died 3&#47;12&#47;89&#45;&#45;between 11 &#38; 12 P. M.&#41;<lb/></p>
            </body>
